   - `DFOP0017890_Advancing_Global_Health_APS_Addendum_E_Uganda.pdf` (Uganda tracks/objectives/principles)
   - Round 1 + Round 2a Q&A PDFs (formatting clarifications; **Addendum E: Uganda** Q&A only)
3. **Ignore** other-country Addenda (D/F/G/H/J) and Addendum I unless FairBanks later expands scope.

## FairBanks scope

- Phase 1 **SOI** for **Addendum E — Uganda**, Window 2a: due **31 July 2026, 5:00 PM EDT**.
- Primary: **Track 2, Objective 4** (interoperable digital health → progressive **GOU ownership**). Name objective(s) clearly.
- Bridge last-mile CHW/VHT data into national stack — not a parallel silo. Align with **NDHA / OpenHIE**, MoH authority, and named systems (eCHIS, EMRs e.g. eAfya/ClinicMaster, DHIS2/eIDSR, National Data Warehouse, iHRIS, LIS as relevant). Document staffing/recurrent-cost transition by close.
- Root in FairBanks cascade; FCHIP = intelligence layer. Win-win for MoH/USG/districts/CHWs/FairBanks. Slogan only: **Your health, our mission.**

## APS Phase 1 SOI package (Word + PDF submission pack)

Official upload is **one English PDF** (Grants.gov or MyGrants). Our Word/PDF must be submission-ready; PPT is a visual companion, same story.

| Piece | Rule |
|---|---|
| Cover | **Required** Table of Critical Details (title, org, Addendum E, Uganda, federal share $, cost share if any, project length ≤5 yrs). Does **not** count toward 5 pages. |
| Narrative | Issue/opportunity; solution/activities; outcomes/results (lives, systems, efficiency, self-reliance, U.S. interest); partners/roles if any; cost share note if any. ≤**5 pages / ~2500 words** excluding tables/charts/diagrams. |
| Format | Letter **8½×11**; **1" margins**; **12-pt Times New Roman**; single-spaced; page numbers. Tables/charts/captions ≥10-pt OK. |
| Annexes | ≤**4**, each ≤**1 page**; supplement only. |
| File name | e.g. `FairBanks – SOI – Addendum E.pdf` |

## Addendum E content checks

Integrate guiding principles: country ownership (no parallel/indefinite TA dependence); protect HIV/TB/malaria/MNCH/immunisation/outbreak continuity; data into GOU systems for action; integrated people-centred care; local GOU/FBO/CBO partners; evidence/context fit; MoH coordination; faith/service separation if FBOs involved.

## Merit criteria (APS §F)

Equal weight: quality of idea; organisational capacity; planning/ability to achieve objectives.

